The Operator Resilience project produces governance-as-code artefacts for
operator authority, cognition, and resilience under adversarial, degraded,
and high-stress conditions. The artefacts are engineering interpretation
and operational discipline; they are not clinical guidance, not legal
advice, and not a substitute for human-factors qualification by competent
authorities or trained occupational practitioners.

DPIA precondition. The Operator Authority Degradation Contract (OADC),
H-state assessment, and duress protocols process personal data including
operator identification and cognitive-state markers. A Data Protection
Impact Assessment under GDPR Article 35 is a precondition for operational
use in EU contexts. See `docs/integration/regulatory-cross-reference.md`.
